{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Description\nLOC/size analyzer that shells to `scc --format json` (deterministic, no network), populating `AnalyzerResult.loc` (per-file/per-language LOC + max). Absent scc -> Unavailable, never fabricated zeros.\n\n## Design: expand-contract sequencing\n1. CONTRACT first: extract the existing scc JSON parse/normalize from `src/rebar/grounding/engine_b_backends.py` (`_metric_invoke` / `_scc_files`) into a shared helper (e.g. `rebar.metrics.analyzers._scc.parse_scc_json`).\n2. Point BOTH the grounding backend and the new `analyzers/scc_loc.py` at that shared helper — no second JSON normalizer.\n\n## Review-driven corrections\n- Reuse the grounding scc seam (do not re-implement JSON parsing).\n- Live in `src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/` (not the quarantined `adapters/`).\n- Absent tool -> reuse `Unavailable(reason, accruing_since)`; `accruing_since` from a module-level `_ACCRUING_SINCE` constant (matching the existing reader modules).\n- Deps are SIBLING stories: 3b30 (interface), 9597 (extra), e7a0 (config scan roots).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `analyzers/scc_loc.py` runs scc over the configured scan root, parses via the shared helper -> per-file/per-language LOC + max_loc.\n- [ ] scc absent / non-zero exit -> `Unavailable(reason, accruing_since)`, not a crash and not zeros.\n- [ ] The shared helper is used by BOTH callers (single normalizer).\n\n## Verification (proof of reuse — the blocking gap)\n- [ ] Unit asserts the reuse by IMPORT: `from rebar.metrics.analyzers._scc import parse_scc_json` AND `engine_b_backends` imports the same symbol (grep/import assertion in the test), proving scc_loc.py does not re-implement normalization.\n- [ ] Unit with a monkeypatched runner seam (no scc needed in CI); integration test skipped if scc absent.\n\n## Dependencies: 3b30, 9597, e7a0 (recorded depends_on edges to all three).\n## Files likely touched: src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/scc_loc.py (new), src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/_scc.py (new shared parse), src/rebar/grounding/engine_b_backends.py (point at shared helper), tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py (new)\n## Estimated scope: M"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784530320168074001,"uuid":"54e63ca6-3475-4edd-8120-5ba6a9f8cfb6"}